    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-06-28T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-06-28T19:00:00-05:00" n="143"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">495A.119/6–2850: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">Certain Diplomatic Missions</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d143fn1">Sent to all diplomatic missions except Bucharest,
                        Budapest, Moscow, Prague. Sofia, and Warsaw.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">plain</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-06-28T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 28, 1950—8 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In order to implement UN SC Resolution of June 27 requesting member governments
                    refrain from giving aid North Korea, US instituted complete embargo of exports
                    to North Korea effective 4 p. m. June 28, 1950. Inform Government to which
                        accredited.<note n="2" xml:id="d143fn2">For documentation on this subject,
                        see <ref target="frus1950v06#pg_256">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">vi</hi>, pp.
                            256</ref> ff.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
